# 🤖 Jarvis-Core: A Personal, Local, Secure AI Assistant

A modular, type-safe, privacy-first AI assistant built with LangGraph, Ollama, PostgreSQL + pgvector, and Express.js. Runs entirely on your machine. No cloud dependencies. No data leaves your control.

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview


🖥️ Your Machine (Kali Linux)
│
├── 🧠 Agent Brain (TypeScript + LangGraph)
│ ├── src/agent/ # State machine: nodes, graph, state
│ ├── src/tools/ # Tool definitions: system_check, rag_query
│ ├── src/security.ts # Allowlist, audit logging, command validation
│ └── src/llm/ # ChatOllama + OllamaEmbeddings
│
├── 🗄️ Infrastructure (Docker)
│ ├── jarvis-db # PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector (port 5433)
│ └── jarvis-cache # Redis (port 6379)
│
├── 🦙 Local LLM (Ollama)
│ ├── llama3:8b-instruct-q4_0 # Chat/completion model
│ └── nomic-embed-text # 768-dim embedding model for RAG
│
└── 🔐 Security & Observability
├── Audit logs (file + PostgreSQL)
├── Command allowlists + pattern blocking
└── JWT-ready auth middleware (for future expansion)




---

## ✅ What Works Right Now

| Feature | Status | How to Test |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| 🧠 Agent Brain (LangGraph) | ✅ Working | `npx tsx src/test-agent.ts` |
| 🔧 Tool Calling (`system_check`) | ✅ Working | Ask: `"Are my Docker containers running?"` |
| 🔐 Security Layer | ✅ Working | Try `"docker rm -rf /"` → blocked + logged |
| 📝 Audit Logging | ✅ Working | Check `audit.log` or `audit_logs` table |
| 🤖 Local LLM (Ollama) | ✅ Working | `curl http://localhost:11434/api/tags` |
| 🧠 RAG Memory (`rag_query`) | ✅ Working | Ask: `"What did I learn about pgvector?"` |
| 💬 Conversational Context | 🟡 Ready | State structure in place; persist to DB next |
| 🔊 Voice Interface | ⚪ Planned | Whisper.cpp + Piper TTS integration pending |

