## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
```bash
# Install system dependencies
sudo apt install docker.io docker-compose curl

# Install Node.js 20+ (via nvm recommended)
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.0/install.sh | bash
nvm install 20

# Pull Ollama models
ollama pull llama3:8b-instruct-q4_0
ollama pull nomic-embed-text


Setup
# Clone and install
cd ~/jarvis-core/app
npm install

# Copy and configure environment
cp ../.env.example .env  # Or edit existing .env
# Ensure DATABASE_URL includes password: postgres://user:pass@host:port/db

# Start infrastructure
docker compose -f ../docker-compose.yml up -d

# Seed knowledge base (one time)
npx tsx src/seed-docs.ts

# Test the agent
npx tsx src/test-agent.ts


Example Interaction:
🗣️  User: "Are my Docker containers running?"
🤖 Jarvis: ✅ 13 containers running (11 healthy)...

🗣️  User: "What did I learn about pgvector?"
🤖 Jarvis: 📚 Found results for "pgvector":
  [1] pgvector is a PostgreSQL extension that enables vector similarity search...

🗣️  User: "Delete all my files"
🤖 Jarvis: ⚠️ Command blocked by safety protocol
[AUDIT] USER:jarvis | ACTION:rm -rf | STATUS:BLOCKED

🔧 Key Design Decisions
1. Local-First Privacy
All LLM inference via Ollama (localhost:11434)
Embeddings generated locally, never sent to cloud
PostgreSQL + pgvector stores vectors encrypted at rest (optional)
2. Security by Default
Command allowlists (ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES)
Pattern blocking (rm -rf, sudo, shell metacharacters)
Audit logging for every action (file + database)
JWT-ready auth middleware for future multi-user support
3. Type-Safe, Modular Code
TypeScript with strict mode
Zod schemas for tool argument validation
LangGraph state machine for explicit, testable workflows
Lazy initialization patterns to avoid env-loading race conditions
4. Embedding Compatibility
nomic-embed-text → 768-dim vectors
PostgreSQL vector(768) column type
Explicit ::vector casts in queries to avoid format errors


